<br>
Please, learn your class, and learn to be observant and learn to communicate and learn to take steps to avoid miscommunication, etc. For instance, move all battle spam into another chat box that is seperate from the one used for communication. Additionally, learn what classes can do what, so that you know what to expect, and you're not like &quot;dur, Shamanz can heel??!11&quot;, and most importantly, realize that this is not an AOL chatroom, and that you *cannot* get away with being a jerk to everyone at your whim.<br>
<br>
Do not spam repeatedly just because nobody sent you a tell in the ten seconds that it has been since you last /auctioned or /shouted. Learn patience, or buy a First Person Shooter. Everquest is not a game to play if you don't have patience. Secondly, higher level does not necessarily mean that you know more about Everquest than the lower level person who is giving you advice. Don't feel offended when people give you advice; it is not shameful to not know everything there is to know, its normal, and we all learned at one point or another, so we all started at the same point.<br>
<br>
Roleplay, or do not roleplay, that is up to you. However, since this *is* a roleplay preferred server, it is generally accepted that you respect those who are roleplaying, and try to not ruin immersion.<br>
<br>
Shout is not your private channel to say hello to everyone that you once grouped with who happens to be in the same zone as you. This is what /tells are for.<br>
<br>
It is *not* roleplaying to talk smack to that level 65 ogre warrior who's standing around in your newbie area. Your character would be scared to death of that ogre, and rightly so, because he could whoop your butt. Good rule to remember: don't talk smack unless you're willing to accept a duel.<br>
<br>
It is *not* defending your city to train guards or the banker to a group of &quot;invaders&quot; who are killing your city's guards. This is against the Play Nice policy, and is considered a jerk thing to do.<br>
<br>
You might beg. There's nothing anyone can do to stop you, but here's a bit of advice: if you want to be successful, *do it in character*. Tell passersby your sad tale about ten kids at home, and the bedridden wife, and how goblins stole your shipment of jumjum juice that you were going to sell in the Bazaar. I would give platinum to someone who told me all of this, but I never give money or spare items to people that just ask &quot;Hey dude can I have some pp plz?&quot;<br>
<br>
Which brings me to my final bit of advice: Don't use shortcuts when trying to type incharacter. &quot;Plz, sir elf, stay n range 4 ur heal&quot; may sound incharacter to you, but it is very distracting to the majority of roleplayers. There is software and freeware that can teach you to type faster, if that is your problem. (And considering this game is all about working with others, and a HUGE part of working with others is communication, and the only way to communicate is through typing, you really have no excuse behind &quot;I can't type well&quot;. If you can't swim, you do not buy membership at a pool... unless you're planning on learning how to swim.<br>
<br>
If you're impatient or lazy to abide by the general ettiquet, which is loosely outline above, you shouldn't be playing Everquest in the first place, because you're going to have less fun and the people around you are going to have less fun. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=703956" target="top">Duergin MacLeod</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, Shaman of 51 Spirits... who's staying that away until he's got his Epic</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phyxious>Phyxious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/7/03 4:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5158.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Attention: Players interested in coming to FV</span><hr size=1> Amen <p>Phyxious Impera,<br>
