<br>
I'd have something to say. Be ready to see almost any kind of RPing. I for myself play an ogre shaman. But my background says I once was saved from a bad shaman roaming the Feerrott by a spirit and since talk with them and do what they ask. What my character call spirits are a lot of things going from the wolf (someone want a SOW), the Boar up to what people use to call god (Rallos Zek, despite being the god of ogres, is only the Great Spirit of War when I RP Klatcrane). Thus I wouldn't say my toon has a god, nor that he has none, he simply has them all and pray for the one suiting the more to the situation where he stands (I won't pray Rallos Zek on a wedding and I won't pray Prexus when I'm in the midle of Lavastorm, you have my point I guess).<br>
<br>
Coming from what I just said (or wrote...), I'd say my toon is neither evil, nor good nor neutral (best way I can explain that in english wich is not my mother tongue) but merely a mix of that all, sometime people will call me evil, sometime they'll associate my name with the most pure of the Gods, but to me Klatcrane follows the spirits and spirits are beyond good or evil, they just ARE (and when you follow a pack of &quot;god&quot; how can you say you are good, evil or neutral as these gods are from various tendencies ?). To be 100% true, the way my toon sees evil or good is a bit strange as these concepts are something he has a hardtime to understand, it's about the same thing as understanding someone who prays only one god/spirit : for Klatcrane, noone can reach the true enlightment if they don't learn to listen to all the spirits, not just some of them.<br>
<br>
Well, this was a bit long and my purpose was : don't be surprised about how you can see people RPing, you might see some strange things such as a necromancer who seeks redemption or studies necromancy to try to bring back his dead love, you might encounter a magician whose sole purpose is mastering the elements and who might believe himself as superior to some gods such as Xegony  for she is the Air...<br>
Now some people will RP, but won't do it hardcore. I used to, but now I'm not RPing 100% of my time, though if someone speaks to me in a RP way, 100% chances are that I will RP with him when speaking with him. When I'm on a raid, don't expect to see me doing a lot of RP, I do what I can if possible.<br>
<br>
Most of all, enjoy your time here and do your possible to have people enjoy their (saying that doesn't mean I'll buff each and every young one asking for it, just that if they ask it in a way that makes me feel more IN game, you can be sure he'lkl got his buffs and even more, if not, he might not have any response).<br>
<br>
Klatcrane,<br>
Talking with spirits since 65th totems <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=danelikfv>DanelikFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/20/03 3:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5158.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Haha</span><hr size=1> &quot;It is not about which class you play, it is about how well you play it.&quot;<br>
